      "writtenOn": "2017-10-17T19:04:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Maybe you created a new context to do a one-shot rendering, and it\u0027s a huge pain to mark every single path as volatile, especially since in a different context the same SkPath is not volatile. Also, paths are the only objects that you can exempt from caching by marking them volatile, so this would be the only way to disable caching for things like masks in a one-shot rendering.",
